<subSubSection id="029FF5D84E191F12EBC5B0FAA58648BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9F1645869FA1C2C8DB7916AEEBDD5C1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D77CDA4BC56CC3F577E6C84447B69BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Smaller body length, usually between 6-9.3 mm; mandibles with only three teeth (plus molar one); pronotum usually as wide as long; elytra 3.3-3.6 times longer than wide, coarsely punctate; aedeagus shape variable, usually very wide, and internal sac shape variable.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
